# Use Cases

Omitted by default. Add a Use Case when **any** of these apply:

- **Shared logic** — the same business operation is needed by two or more Cubits or features
- **Complex orchestration** — operation involves multiple repositories, data transformations, or domain rules that don't belong in the Cubit
- **Independent testability** — a critical business rule that warrants its own unit test, separate from cubit and repository tests

**Do not add** a Use Case for simple repository calls (fetch / save / delete) where the Cubit just delegates and maps state.

## Folder placement

```
lib/features/<feature>/
  data/               ← unchanged
  domain/
    usecases/         get_active_orders_use_case.dart
  view/               ← unchanged
  viewModel/          ← Cubit injects UseCase, not Repository
```

## Template

```dart
class GetActiveOrdersUseCase {
  final OrderRepository _orders;
  final UserRepository _users;

  GetActiveOrdersUseCase({
    required OrderRepository orders,
    required UserRepository users,
  })  : _orders = orders,
        _users = users;

  Future<Either<Failure, List<Order>>> call(String userId) async {
    final userResult = await _users.getUser(userId);
    return userResult.fold(
      left,
      (user) => _orders.getActiveOrders(userId: user.id, role: user.role),
    );
  }
}
```

## DI registration (when a Use Case is added)

```dart
injector.registerFactory(
  () => GetActiveOrdersUseCase(
    orders: injector<OrderRepository>(),
    users: injector<UserRepository>(),
  ),
);
injector.registerFactory(
  () => OrdersCubit(getActiveOrders: injector<GetActiveOrdersUseCase>()),
);
```
